##Acessesing Elements:

1.by id :
use for acess element by html id.
let heading = document.getElementById("id name");
console.log(heading);
console.dir(heading);

2.by class:
use for acess element by html class.
let p = document.getElementsByClassName("header");
console.log(p);

3.by tag:
we can acess tham by adding tag name.
let a = document.getElementsByTagName('tag name')

4. by query:
you can use it for all of them like by id class or tag.
for class use dot(.) before it and for id use # before but all function will not work in id cuz its make no sence.

const firstButton = document.querySelector("button"); // first match
const allButtons = document.querySelectorAll("button"); // NodeList of all buttons


